From Andre Molyneux Subject Re LCIII PowerPC In article David Joshua Mirsky writes I own an LCIII and I recently heard an interesting I heard that the LCIII has a built in slot for a PowerPC Is this true I heard that the slot is not the same as the PDS Is that true Thanks David Mirsky Well I also have an LC Popping the top revealed One socket for an additional VRAM SIMM One socket for a pin RAM SIMM One socket for a flat pack FPU A processor direct slot PDS identical to the LC LC II but with an additional set of connetions to one side for the full bit data path that the LC LC II lacked That's I guess a board with a PowerPC chip could be made that would fit in the PDS but that's the only Andre Molyneux Insert your favorite disclaimer here PYRAMID TECHNOLOGY CORP Internet First Street San Jose CA Packet